## Enhancement Layer — Apply After All Screens Are Built

### Point 1: Empty States
Every screen that displays a list or data container must have a designed empty state.
Empty states must include: an illustration or icon, a headline ("No items yet"),
a one-sentence explanation, and a single primary CTA to create the first item.
Do NOT show a blank white area. Do NOT show "No data found."

### Point 2: Loading States
Every async data fetch must show a skeleton UI during loading — not a spinner.
The skeleton must match the shape of the loaded content (same number of rows,
same card dimensions). Apply this to: all list screens, all detail screens,
all dashboard widgets.

### Point 3: Error States
Every screen that makes a network request must handle failure gracefully.
Show: an error icon, a plain-language message ("Could not load your data"),
and a "Try again" button that retries the request.
Never show a raw error code or stack trace to the user.

### Point 4: Micro-animations
Apply these specific transitions:
- List items: fade-in stagger (50ms delay between items, 200ms duration)
- Modal/drawer open: slide-up from bottom on mobile, fade+scale on desktop
- Button press: 96% scale for 100ms on active state
- Page transitions: 150ms fade between routes
- Form success: green checkmark animation on submit

